Mexican PRD Opts Out of Alliance With PAN, El Universal Says

-- B y   A d r i a n a   L o p e z   C a r a v e o
-- 
2011-04-11T14:53:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/mexican-prd-opts-out-of-alliance-with-pan-el-universal-says.html
Mexico ’s opposition Party of the
Democratic Revolution, or PRD, opted out of its alliance with
President Felipe Calderon’s  National Action Party , or PAN, for
the governor’s race in the State of Mexico,  El Universal 
newspaper reported.  The PRD instead approved a coalition with the  Labor Party 
and Convergence Party, and the alliance will headed by the PRD’s
Alejandro Encinas, the Mexico City-based newspaper said.  The PAN and PRD have previously succeeded with alliance
candidates in states where the  Institutional Revolutionary
Party , or PRI, had never been defeated, including Oaxaca,
Puebla, Sinaloa and Guerrero in the last eight months.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adriana Lopez Caraveo in Mexico City at 
 adrianalopez@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
